The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Golden melodies

 With the passage of time, the enchanting melodies of Bengali songs of the yesteryear lie all but forgotten. Presented by Dimension Four, this evening?s solo recital of Bengali songs by Nupurchhanda Ghosh represents a sincere effort to carry forward the magic of these lost melodies to the new generation of music lovers. Featuring songs of Atulprosad Sen, Rajanikanto Sen, Dwijendralal Roy and Dilip Kumar Roy, as well as kirtans (devotional songs), Ghosh?s rendition will cover the entire range of the compositions of these music legends. Revealing the full depth and versatility of her vocal prowess, she will perform the tappa and thumri of Atulprosad?s lyrics, Rajanikanto?s devotional songs in praise of Mother Goddess, and patriotic and theatre songs of Dwijendralal. Pradip Ghosh and Sunil Bhandari will narrate the works of these poet-lyricists in Bengali and English, respectively.

 Event: Bengali songs by Nupurchhanda Ghosh

 When: Today at 6.45 pm

 Where: Sisir Mancha




